{
  "stem": "25639.5",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "If I jumped off, I might be able to save myself and perhaps see my mother again, and my sister, too.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when that truck approached that familiar wooded area, where there was a deep ditch near the road, I jumped off the slow moving truck, and I leaped down the embankment.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And at the bottom, there was a culvert.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I couldn't see that from the roadside.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was too far down to be seen.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I could tell that there was a deep ditch, as we marched to work each day and marched back at night.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I crawled into this culvert.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I stayed there that night, the following day, and until the following night-- in the middle of the night some time-- without any food or clothing.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In fact, soft ice formed along the sides of the water that ran through the culvert.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there I was.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "After about 15 minutes or so, I heard the sirens go on, which meant-- to alert the guards, that the guards had to be alerted.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in another 15 minutes or so-- I don't know exactly, of course-- I heard the voices of German men.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And obviously the guards, they were looking for me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But after a while, the commotion had died down.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I stayed in this culvert for about 24 hours, roughly, without any food or clothing.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Then I decided that if I stayed in that culvert, I am going to die, simply from the cold-- from the elements, and from starvation.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now I'd like to go back a few steps.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "While we were still on the truck, I said, 'Who will come with me?' And nobody responded.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Everyone was completely emaciated and robbed of all energy and willpower-- in fact, probably even the very last shred of hope.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
